# .herd/links — cross-repo link registry. Commit this (code-shaped config, zero-secret).
# Each line defines a named peer repo target:
#
#   name|owner/repo|backend|tracker_target
#
#   name            short identifier used with:  herd report --to <name>
#   owner/repo      repository slug (same format as HERD_REPO and gh -R)
#   backend         adapter: github | linear | file | changelog
#   tracker_target  optional extra routing info (e.g. Linear team ID); leave blank for most backends
#
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# Run 'herd link list' to see active entries.
#
# Example:
#   engine|owner/upstream-repo|github|
